    String token = userService.authenticateUser(credentials.getEmail(), credentials.getPassword());
    if (token != null) {
        return Response.ok(token).build();
    } else {
        return Response.status(Response.Status.UNAUTHORIZED).build();
    }
}
```

3. For the other endpoints that require authentication (e.g., `getAllUsers`, `getUserById`, `updateUser`, `deleteUser`), you need to check if the incoming request has a valid JWT token. You can create a method in the `AuthenticationService` to validate the token:

